is a leading indicator for traffic,

291
00:15:56,807 --> 00:15:59,227
meaning the users that were acquired

292
00:15:59,347 --> 00:16:01,108
and the change in rate at which they were acquired

293
00:16:01,508 --> 00:16:03,648
happened earlier than this growth.

294
00:16:04,129 --> 00:16:06,229
So when we look back at when it really changed,

295
00:16:06,349 --> 00:16:09,530
it was actually August and September the year before

296
00:16:09,550 --> 00:16:11,731
where we started to see this uptick

297
00:16:12,311 --> 00:16:13,411
in new user acquisition.

298
00:16:14,171 --> 00:16:17,632
So that unfortunately invalidates Xbox, that's the theory.

299
00:16:21,163 --> 00:16:25,665
So this is where things get a little bit more murky,

300
00:16:26,626 --> 00:16:27,667
but super important.

301
00:16:29,908 --> 00:16:31,529
There was a really fundamental change

302
00:16:31,989 --> 00:16:33,590
we made on our platform in 2014,

303
00:16:33,990 --> 00:16:37,893
and we call it DevEx, or developer exchange.

304
00:16:38,993 --> 00:16:42,335
This is the ability for the creators on our platform

305
00:16:43,015 --> 00:16:44,496
to take money out.

306
00:16:45,817 --> 00:16:48,979
So up until this time, for the previous eight years,

307
00:16:50,628 --> 00:16:53,270
They'd been working in a way where they'd make content

308
00:16:53,470 --> 00:16:56,191
and share it, and they'd get some virtual currency back.

309
00:16:56,972 --> 00:16:58,473
But it would just accumulate in their account.

310
00:16:59,273 --> 00:17:01,955
They could spend it on things on Roblox, but that was it.

311
00:17:03,456 --> 00:17:06,998
In 2014, we said, OK, you guys can take that out

312
00:17:07,178 --> 00:17:08,479
for cold, hard cash.

313
00:17:10,080 --> 00:17:12,682
And this was actually a really hard decision when we made it,

314
00:17:13,122 --> 00:17:16,824
because we already had this huge community there producing

315
00:17:16,864 --> 00:17:17,565
tons of content.

316
00:17:17,865 --> 00:17:19,186
Clearly, people liked the content.

317
00:17:20,563 --> 00:17:24,289
Why would we give them money when they'll do it for free?

318
00:17:25,170 --> 00:17:28,916
But what we've seen is this is probably the best decision we ever made,

319
00:17:29,637 --> 00:17:33,724
because it changed the whole nature of how people make content on the platform.

320
00:17:34,678 --> 00:17:37,080
They started to take it much more professionally.

321
00:17:37,501 --> 00:17:39,303
These people who had built up all these skills

322
00:17:39,383 --> 00:17:43,167
and connections and community began to create

323
00:17:43,627 --> 00:17:45,770
in a much more serious manner.

324
00:17:46,450 --> 00:17:48,593
And that produced a level of game quality

325
00:17:49,013 --> 00:17:50,955
that far outstripped what we had before.

326
00:17:52,427 --> 00:17:56,248
So this is actually very difficult to chart

327
00:17:57,069 --> 00:17:59,630
because it happened over a period of years.

328
00:18:00,510 --> 00:18:04,251
But what we see is a combined network effect.

329
00:18:05,111 --> 00:18:06,412
We have two network effects here

330
00:18:06,452 --> 00:18:07,832
that are feeding off of each other.

331
00:18:09,053 --> 00:18:11,173
There's a community of creators.

332
00:18:11,853 --> 00:18:13,934
And we see the more creators there are,

333
00:18:14,254 --> 00:18:15,555
the better it is for each creator

334
00:18:15,595 --> 00:18:18,756
because they can form these teams and groups of people

335
00:18:18,816 --> 00:18:21,337
and work collaboratively to create awesome content.

336
00:18:22,917 --> 00:18:24,278
And then the better content they make,

337
00:18:25,138 --> 00:18:26,298
we have the player community,

338
00:18:26,558 --> 00:18:27,879
and they have their own network effect

339
00:18:27,899 --> 00:18:29,059
where the more players there are,

340
00:18:29,779 --> 00:18:31,780
the better an experience it is for each player.

341
00:18:32,900 --> 00:18:34,341
And these two things feed off each other.

342
00:18:35,341 --> 00:18:39,743
So I do believe this was a factor in our growth change,

343
00:18:40,623 --> 00:18:42,724
although it's something that happened

344
00:18:42,764 --> 00:18:43,904
over a long period of time,

345
00:18:44,784 --> 00:18:48,246
and probably can't be a sharp uptick in itself.

346
00:18:50,966 --> 00:18:51,086
So,

347
00:18:52,685 --> 00:18:54,345
Back to our theories.

